{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0972cd9e-94f0-4bd8-9021-99efb5c3d644","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. Here's what you need to change conceptually:\n\n### 1. **NuGet.org setup**\n- Go to **NuGet.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new trusted publisher, specifying your GitHub repo, branch/tag filters, and the workflow/environment name.\n\n### 2. **Workflow changes**\n\n**Add `id-token` permission** so the runner can request an OIDC token:\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Instead of passing `--api-key`:\n\n```yaml\n# Before (API key)\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# After (trusted publishing / OIDC)\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: \"\"          # clear any old token\n```\n\nActually, the simplest path is to use the **`dotnet nuget push` with `--api-key` still**, but obtain a short-lived token via OIDC. NuGet's current trusted-publishing flow works like this:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (OIDC)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n      --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nWith trusted publishing configured on NuGet.org **and** `id-token: write` set, the NuGet client automatically negotiates the OIDC exchange — no `--api-key` or secret needed.\n\n### 3. **Use an environment** (recommended)\nAdd an `environment:` to the job for an extra approval gate and to scope the OIDC trust:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish   # matches what you set on NuGet.org\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n```\n\n### Summary of changes\n| Area | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| NuGet.org | API key | Trusted publisher entry |\n| Workflow permissions | _(default)_ | `id-token: write` |\n| Push command | `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | no key needed |\n| Secret | `NUGET_API_KEY` | can be **deleted** |\n| Job environment | _(optional)_ | recommended for scoping |\n\nIf you paste your workflow file, I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec7644ac-6b49-458b-8f75-24ef9f5e35b9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"C80B:852E1:B6397:E548A:69F54B94"},"id":"df7c1042-e544-4573-8bc7-e9409fec9482","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:56:05.029Z","parentId":"39626324-5e5f-4194-b8ae-5402071c3c07"}
